article.description: — Malachi Smith had 28 points as Chattanooga beat Tennessee Tech 82-65 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Smith lifts Chattanooga over Tennessee Tech 82-65
article.linkText: Smith lifts Chattanooga over Tennessee Tech 82-65
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- — Malachi Smith had 28 points as Chattanooga beat Tennessee Tech 82-65 on Tuesday night. Smith hit 11 of 14 shots. He added six rebounds. David Jean-Baptiste had 18 points and six assists for Chattanooga (6-1). Silvio De Sousa added 17 points and 11 rebounds. A.J. Caldwell had six assists. Amadou Sylla had 12 points for the Golden Eagles (2-5). Kenny White Jr. added 11 points. Jr. Clay had 10 points and six assists. The Mocs improve to 2-0 against the Golden Eagles on the season. Chattanooga defeated Tennessee Tech 69-62 on Nov. 16. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
